# Day 3 - TCP Three-Way Handshake

## Objective
Learn how TCP establishes a reliable connection before data is exchanged.

## What I Learned
- TCP stands for Transmission Control Protocol.
- TCP is connection-oriented.
- The client starts the connection.
- The server replies with SYN-ACK.
- The client finishes the handshake with ACK.
- After the handshake, TLS begins encrypting communication.

## Wireshark Filters Used
tcp
tcp.stream == 7
tcp.flags.syn == 1

## Skills Practiced
- Capturing TCP traffic
- Identifying SYN packets
- Identifying SYN-ACK packets
- Identifying ACK packets
- Following a TCP stream

## Reflection
Today I learned how every secure website first creates a TCP connection before encrypted communication begins. Seeing the three-way handshake in Wireshark helped me understand how computers establish reliable communication.
